  "text": "This work extends our previous research on air−water interfacial behavior in capillary channels [CITATION_1] by examining the physical origin of the observed limited mobility of the smallscale air−water interface. Particle tracking by means of confocal microscopy enabled the experimental determination of air− water interfacial shapes and flow velocity profiles in open rectangular microchannels with a range of opening sizes (0.6− 5.0 mm). The results were compared with theoretical analyses that examined the influence of the air−water interfacial shape and boundary conditions on the flow pattern in open-square channels.",
